A4.text: Yangon was the capital of Myanmar until 2005 and served as such until 2006.

A5.text: The national capital was moved from Yangon to a site near Pyinmana in November 2005.

A6.text: The military junta officially named the new capital Naypyidaw on 27 March 2006.

A7.text: Although many capitals are defined by constitution or legislation, many long-time capitals have no such legal designation, including Bern, Edinburgh, Lisbon, London, Paris, and Wellington.
